pageTitle: Chie Hayasaka Athlete Profile | The Official Site of BYU Athletics
textAfterTable: Freshman Sophomore Junior Senior 2006-2007 | Freshman Year 9-4 singles record in the fall season Lost to No. 79 Liz Ferris from Utah in a three set tiebreak at the Wilson/ITA Central-West Regional Championships Teamed with Dolly Chang to rack up 10 wins and 2 losses in the fall season in doubles, winning flight 2 of the BYU Invitational Competed at Nos. 3, 4 and 5 in singles competition during the spring season with winning records at each position Compiled a 15-10 spring singles record and a 24-14 singles record on the year Saw limited doubles action in the spring to compile a 2-3 record with a 10-6 doubles record on the year 2007-2008 | Sophomore Year Named to the Academic All-MWC team Finished the fall season with a 1-2 record in both singles and doubles Competed at the Nos. 2, 3, 4 and 5 positions in the Cougar lineup during the spring season, compiling an 11-14 singles record Began Mountain West Conference play with a five-match winning streak Competed with Elle Carney at No. 3 doubles for the majority of the spring season, during which the duo earned a 10-5 record 2008-2009 | Junior Year
